div.div:
(1) Think of the UI layer as dumb, empty shell. Like a Mechanical Turk, it needs something else to tell it what to do in response to user events.
(2) The UI layer does this by providing an API that some sort of "application engine" can use to manipulate it.
(3) All the UI layer does in response to a user action is to fire an event describing the action.
(4) The "engine" (whatever it may be) is expected to listen to this event, decide what to do and control the UI using provided API function calls.
